Drinking Buddy		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Teamwork																						DESC:You and your allies have almost preternatural luck when you've all had a few drinks.		SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BENEFIT:Once per day, if you are drunk (or worse) within 10 feet of an ally who has this feat and is also drunk (or worse), you can reroll one d20 roll as a free action. You must take the result of the second roll, even if it is worse.
Drunken God's Blessings	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	PREDEITY:1,Cayden Cailean														DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Cayden Cailean smiles upon you when you visit his most favored temples-taverns.		SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BENEFIT:When you have had at least a number of drinks equal to your Constitution modifier (or get drunk or soused, if you are using the rules on pages 54-55) in a tavern, once within the following 24 hours, you can gain the benefits of remove paralysis as a free action. Alternatively, you can choose one of the following benefits depending on the type of bar you patronized. At the GM's discretion, other types of taverns might grant other benefits. [Gambling Den] You can gain the benefits of detect thoughts for 1 minute as a free action. [Illegal Tavern] You can gain the benefits of invisibility for 1 minute as a free action. [Posh Tavern] You can gain the benefits of eagle's splendor for 1 minute as a free action. [Private Club] You can gain the benefits of undetectable alignment for 1 minute as a free action. [Rowdy Bar] You can gain the benefits of bear's endurance for 1 minute as a free action. [Tavern of Intrigue] You can gain the benefits of fox's cunning for 1 minute as a free action.
Drunken Sing-Along	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	PRESKILL:2,Diplomacy=1,Perform (Sing)=1															DESC:With a raised tankard and catchy tune, you can get large groups of people on your side.	SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:While in a tavern or other drinking establishment, you can change the attitude of the patrons from unfriendly to indifferent or from indifferent to friendly by spending 10 minutes engaging in a group sing-along. For the following 24 hours, your attempts to gather information in that tavern take only 2d6 minutes if the patrons are indifferent or 1d4 minutes if the patrons are friendly. You must be able to speak the same language as the majority of the patrons to use this feat. [Special] You can use this feat with a large crowd of people outside of a tavern if you supply at least 5 gp worth of alcohol to the group.
Extreme Mood Swings	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																						DESC:Your emotions sometimes get the better of you.								SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:Increase each morale bonus you receive by 1. You take a âˆ’1 penalty on saves against emotion and fear effects. When you are drunk (or worse), this penalty doubles, but you increase each morale bonus you receive by 2 instead.
Hardy Liver			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Great Fortitude														DESC:You can hold your liquor and poisons better than most.							SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on Fortitude saving throws against ingested poisons. You take no penalties when you are tipsy, and the penalties for being drunk or soused are halved for you.
Implacable			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Combat																							DESC:You aren't easily fazed, especially when you've been drinking.					SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on saving throws against pain effects. When you are drunk or soused, you gain DR 5/piercing or slashing.
Muddled Morals		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																						DESC:Your conviction is strong... unless you've had a few drinks.						SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on saving throws against effects that affect you based on your alignment. In addition, choose an alignment one step away from your true alignment; when you are drunk (or worse), spells and other effects affect you as if this alignment were your alignment.
Read the Room		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Drunken Sing-Along	PRESKILL:3,Diplomacy=1,Perform (Sing)=1,Sense Motive=1				DESC:You can gain some insight into the mood of a crowd with just a look.				SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:Before you use the Drunken Sing-Along feat, you can attempt a DC 20 Sense Motive check as a free action to pick the exact right song for that crowd. If you are successful, you gain a +4 circumstance bonus on your next Diplomacy check to gather information in that tavern.
Tavern Regular		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_CHA,14																DESC:You are quite popular at the pubs you frequent and the bartenders remember you.		SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BENEFIT:You receive a 10%% discount at any tavern after you have spent a cumulative 500 gp there. In addition, if a bar fight occurs in that tavern, you gain a +2 bonus on your checks to use the redirect action. On a round in which you don't attempt the redirect action, the crowd reduces your tenacity by only 1d4 (instead of by the normal amount).
